This Statement shows that KKZAP promises to protect the user privacy information. In view of the features of online website, KKZAP will interact with users inevitably. So, the statement of Privacy applies to the company and the user and governs data collection and usage. By using the KKZAP Websites, you consent to the data practices described in this statement.
Collection of non-Personal Information
Non-personal information means that these data do not directly identify the user. Information about your computer hardware and software may be collected by KKZAP, such as, type of operating devices, offering access to your ISP`s domain name. By collecting these information, KKZAP also carry out traffic statistics, so as to improve the management and services.
Collection of Personal Information
KKZAP may also collect anonymous demographic information, which is not unique to you, such as your email address. We may gather additional personal or non-personal information in the future.
When you log in our website, it needs to provides some information about yours, with your consent and confirmation, we will collect your personal information through registration forms and other forms. These information maybe include: your basic information( name, sex, age, the date of birth, ID number, Tel No., address, email address ), social networking basic profile information(Apps have a basic connection to a user's Facebook account to ask for permission to post on the user's behalf or to read other fields from the user's timeline or their friends' timelines),Request read permissions (to fill the stream with photos, the user must grant the app two "read permissions" that let the app read the user's photos and their friends' photos), Request publish permissions (the user must grant the app a "publish permission" to share photos).
These information are used for the operation of the services, to maintain quality of the service, and to provide general statistics regarding use of the KKZAP website. Please be aware that KKZAP cannot provides your personal information for other purposes or the third parties without your consent and confirmation.
